150":"1150年","1095":"1095年","Norfolk, England":"英国英格兰諾福爾可","Normandy, France":"法国諾門迪","lifeSummary":"Agnes Fitzwalter于1097年出生在法国諾門迪。她和Robert de Vallibus至少有1个儿子。她去世于1140年在英国英格兰諾福爾可享年43岁。"},"hr":{"1097–1140":"1097.–1140.","1095–1154":"1095–1154","1117–1150":"1117–1150","1117":"1117","about 1117":"oko 1117.","1154":"1154","1097":"1097.","1140":"1140.","1150":"1150","1095":"1095","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, Engleska, United Kingdom","Normandy, France":"Normandie, Francuska"},"cs":{"1097–1140":"1097–1140","1095–1154":"1095–1154","1117–1150":"1117–1150","1117":"1117","about 1117":"okolo 1117","1154":"1154","1097":"1097","1140":"1140","1150":"1150","1095":"1095","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, Anglie, United Kingdom","Normandy, France":"Normandie, Francie"},"da":{"1097–1140":"1097–1140","1095–1154":"1095–1154","1117–1150":"1117–1150","1117":"1117","about 1117":"omkring 1117","1154":"1154","1097":"1097","1140":"1140","1150":"1150","1095":"1095","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","Normandy, France":"Normandie, Frankrig"},"nl":{"1097–1140":"1097–1140","1095–1154":"1095–1154","1117–1150":"1117–1150","1117":"1117","about 1117":"circa 1117","1154":"1154","1097":"1097","1140":"1140","1150":"1150","1095":"1095","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Normandy, France":"Normandie, Frankrijk"},"en":{"1097–1140":"1097–1140","1095–1154":"1095–1154","1117–1150":"1117–1150","1117":"1117","about 1117":"about 1117","1154":"1154","1097":"1097","1140":"1140","1150":"1150","1095":"1095","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","Normandy, France":"Normandy, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Fitzwalter","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["Norman, English, Irish: relationship name from Anglo-Norman French  <i>fiz</i> ‘son’ (  see  Fitz  ) + the personal name   Walter  , ‘son of  <i>Walter</i>’."],"variants":[{"name":"Fitzwater","meanings":["Irish: altered form of <b>Fitzwalter</b>, a patronymic from Anglo-Norman French <i>fi(t)z</i> ‘son’ (see   Fitz  ) + the personal name   Walter  , meaning ‘son of <i>Walter</i>’.","History: This is the name of a family of Norman origin, descended from Godfrey, Count of Brionne (died <i>c.</i> 1010). Godfrey's grandson, Richard FitzGilbert, accompanied William the Conqueror and was made Lord of Clare. His great-grandson was Robert FitzWalter, one of the barons who guaranteed the Magna Carta in 1215."]},{"name":"Walter","meanings":["English (of Norman origin), German, Dutch, Polish, Swedish, and Danish: from a personal name composed of the ancient Germanic elements <i>wald</i> ‘rule’ + <i>heri</i>, <i>hari</i> ‘army’. This personal name was introduced into England both in the reign of Edward the Confessor and by the Normans (in the forms <i>Walt(i)er</i>, <i>Waut(i)er</i>). After the Norman Conquest it soon became one of the most popular personal names in Britain. Compare   Walther  .","Germanized or Americanized form of Czech, Slovak, Croatian, and Slovenian <b>Valter</b> and Czech <b>Valtr</b>: from the personal name <i>Valter</i>, <i>Valtr</i>, of ancient Germanic origin (see 1 above)."]},{"name":"Fitz","meanings":["English: from Anglo-Norman French <i>fi(t)z</i> ‘son’ (from Latin <i>filius</i>), used originally to distinguish a son from a father bearing the same personal name and then conventionalized as a hereditary surname, or short for a surname of which <i>fiz</i> ‘son’ was the first element, for example   Fitzhenry   and   Fitzroy  .","Altered form of English   Fitch  .","German: from a vernacular pet form of the personal name <i>Vinzenz</i> (see   Vincent  ) or <i>Vitus</i> (see   Vito  , compare   Veit  ). Compare also   Fietz  ."]}]},{"name":"Agnes","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Latinized version of the Greek name <i>Hagnē</i>, from the feminine form of the adjective <i>hagnos</i> ‘pure, holy’. This was the name of a young Roman virgin martyred in the persecutions instigated by the Roman emperor Diocletian in   ad  303 . She became a very popular saint in the Middle Ages. Her name was early associated with Latin <i>agnus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Agnes Fitzwalter was born in 1097, in Normandy, France. She had at least 1 son with Robert de Vallibus. She died in 1140, in Norfolk, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 43."},"et":{"1097–1140":"1097–1140","1095–1154":"1095–1154","1117–1150":"1117–1150","1117":"1117","about 1117":"umbes 1117","1154":"1154","1097":"1097","1140":"1140","1150":"1150","1095":"1095","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Normandy, France":"Normandie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1097–1140":"1097–1140","1095–1154":"1095–1154","1117–1150":"1117–1150","1117":"1117","about 1117":"noin 1117","1154":"1154","1097":"1097","1140":"1140","1150":"1150","1095":"1095","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Normandy, France":"Normandie, Ranska"},"fr":{"1097–1140":"1097–1140","1095–1154":"1095–1154","1117–1150":"1117–1150","1117":"1117","about 1117":"environ 1117","1154":"1154","1097":"1097","1140":"1140","1150":"1150","1095":"1095","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Normandy, France":"Normandie, France","lifeSummary":"Agnes Fitzwalter est née en 1097, à Normandie, France. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Robert de Vallibus. Elle est décédée en 1140, à Norfolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, à l’âge de 43 ans."},"de":{"1097–1140":"1097–1140","1095–1154":"1095–1154","1117–1150":"1117–1150","1117":"1117","about 1117"